{"cursor":"3187","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\nA '[[Decision making|decision]] method' is a formal (axiomatic) system that\ncontains at least one action axiom. An action is of the form \"IF  is true,\nTHEN do \". An action axiom tests a condition (antecedent) and, if the\ncondition has been met, then (consequent) it suggests (mandates) an action.\nItalic textFrom knowledge to actionItalic text. Excepting very simple\nsituations, successful action axioms are used in an iterative manner. For\nexample, for decision analysis, the sole action axiom occurs it the Evaluation\nstage of a four-step cycle: Formulate, Evaluate, Interpret/Appraise, Refine.\n","linknr":118,"url":"Decision_model","recorded":1364146471,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Decision_model&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Decision_model&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/Appraisal_(disambiguation)","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Decision_model&action=edit","/wiki/Talk:Decision_model","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Decisio